+-----------------------------------------------------------------------
| Running ${PKGSTEM} on OpenBSD
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Visualizing public measurements without a RIPE Atlas account
============================================================

An account is necessary to create measurements. For more information
about RIPE Atlas, see: https://atlas.ripe.net/

Built-in measurements
---------------------
For a list of build-in public measurements, see:
https://atlas.ripe.net/docs/built-in/

Searching for public measurements
---------------------------------
$ ripe-atlas measurement-search --type ping

Examples
========
Report which instance of k.root-servers.net probes are reaching:
----------------------------------------------------------------
$ ripe-atlas report 10301

Stream IPv4 ping results to k.root-servers.net:
-----------------------------------------------
$ ripe-atlas stream 1001

Stream IPv6 ping results to k.root-servers.net:
-----------------------------------------------
$ ripe-atlas stream 2001

IPv4 traceroute report towards k.root-servers.net from AS 3333:
---------------------------------------------------------------
$ ripe-atlas report --probe-asns 3333 5001

IPv6 traceroute report towards k.root-servers.net from AS 3333:
---------------------------------------------------------------
$ ripe-atlas report --probe-asns 3333 6001
